Caterpillar Financial Services Corporation Key Developments

Caterpillar Financial Announces Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 25 17
Caterpillar Financial announced earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company's revenues of $676 million, an increase of $17 million, or 3%, compared with the second quarter of 2016. Profit was $114 million, a $12 million, or 12%, increase from the second quarter of 2016. The increase in Revenue was due to a $14 million favorable impact from lending activity with Caterpillar, a $13 million favorable impact from higher average financing rates and an $8 million favorable impact from returned or repossessed equipment.  These favorable impacts were partially offset by an $18 million unfavorable impact from lower average earning assets. Profit before income taxes was $164 million for the second quarter of 2017, compared with $148 million for the second quarter of 2016. The increase was primarily due to a $20 million decrease in provision for credit losses, a $10 million favorable impact from miscellaneous revenue items primarily due to lending activity with Caterpillar and an $8 million favorable impact from returned or repossessed equipment. These favorable impacts were partially offset by a $12 million increase in general, operating and administrative expenses primarily due to higher incentive compensation and a $9 million unfavorable impact from lower average earning assets.

For the six months, the company's revenues were $1,338 million compared with $1,302 million a year ago. Profit before income taxes was $331 million compared with $293 million a year ago. Profit was $229 million compared with $202 million a year ago.


Caterpillar Financial Services Corporation Reports Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
Apr 25 17
Caterpillar Financial Services Corporation reported earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, revenues were $662 million against $643 million a year ago. Profit before income taxes was $167 million against $145 million a year ago. Profit was $115 million against $100 million a year ago. The increase was primarily due to a $13 million decrease in provision for credit losses and a $9 million favorable impact from miscellaneous revenue items.


Caterpillar Financial Services Corporation Reports Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Full Year Ended December 31, 2016
Jan 26 17
Caterpillar Financial Services Corporation reported earnings results for the fourth quarter and full year ended December 31, 2016. For the quarter, the company reported revenues of USD 642 million compared to USD 648 million a year ago. Profit before income taxes was USD 122 million compared to USD 129 million a year ago. Profit was USD 85 million compared to USD 114 million a year ago. The decrease in Revenue was primarily due to a USD 19 million unfavorable impact from lower average earning assets and a USD 13 million unfavorable impact from returned or repossessed equipment, partially offset by a USD 24 million favorable impact from higher average financing rates. The decrease in profit before income tax was primarily due to a USD 13 million unfavorable impact from returned or repossessed equipment, a USD 9 million unfavorable impact from lower average earning assets and a USD 9 million increase in provision for credit losses. These unfavorable impacts were partially offset by a decrease of USD 22 million in other operating expenses primarily driven by the absence of employee separation charges that were recorded in the prior year. The provision for income taxes reflects an annual tax rate of 30% for 2016, compared with 26% for 2015. The increase in the annual tax rate is primarily due to a reduction in available foreign tax credits and changes in the geographic mix of profits.

For the year, the company reported revenues of USD 2,595 million compared to USD 2,673 million a year ago. Profit before income taxes was USD 561 million compared to USD 619 million a year ago. Profit was USD 384 million compared to USD 460 million a year ago. The decrease in Revenue was primarily due to a USD 66 million unfavorable impact from lower average earning assets and a USD 43 million unfavorable impact from returned or repossessed equipment, partially offset by a USD 33 million favorable impact from higher average financing rates. The decrease in profit before income tax was primarily due to a USD 43 million unfavorable impact from returned or repossessed equipment and a USD 30 million unfavorable impact from lower average earning assets, partially offset by a USD 24 million decrease in general, operating and administrative expenses.


