ant hydroelectric complex would take 10 years to complete.                      News  Electric Power Brazil  Ituango hydro investment hits US$500mn in H1, says EPM  In a first-half earnings statement, EPM said around half of its total first-half investment outlay went towards construction of the 2.4GW plant, which will be Colombia's largest hydroelectric facility when completed next year.                       News  Banking Argentina  Facial recognition banking coming to Argentina  The Argentine unit of Chinese lender ICBC is poised to start offering the service within a week.                       News  ICT Argentina  Pay-TV business boosts AT&T revenues despite falling subs  AT&T reported revenues of US$2bn in Latin America and 13.6mn pay-TV connections in 2Q17, down 56,000 from the previous quarter.                       News  Water & Waste Brazil  Public hearing on Rio de Janeiro utility's future finishes in confusion  Rio de Janeiro government is planning to privatize the company, but the hearing was disrupted and ended inconclusively.                      News  Mining Brazil  Mining code reforms seen addressing Brazil's revenue needs  But the hike in royalties was not well received by local mining companies, independent analyst Pedro Galdi tells BNamericas.                       News  Insurance Mexico  Mexican pension regulator seeks expanded powers  Greater powers are sought by the pension system authority to better regulate the Afore pension managers, which have come under strong criticism after being hit with major sanctions in April.                       Feature  ICT Argentina  Spotlight: Fintech business verticals in LAC   Financial technology remains a young but rapidly evolving industry, but keeping abreast of the latest trends can be challenging. To help, BNamericas has compiled a basic guide to major business verticals in the fintech ecosystem.                       News  ICT Regional  Zoho to challenge large CRM players in LatAm SME space  Costing U